## 7. Naming Conventions

### 7.1 Files and Directories

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Python modules | `snake_case.py` | `task_orchestrator.py` |
| Directories | lowercase singular/plural matching domain | `agents/`, `memory/` |
| Data files | `snake_case.json` | `titan_state.json` |
| Rule files | `lowercase.mdc` | `titan.mdc` |

### 7.2 Classes

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Managers | `{Domain}Manager` | `StateManager` |
| Agents | `{Domain}Agent` | `CodingAgent` |
| Tools | `{Name}Tool` | `TimeTool` |
| Core app | `Titan` | — |
| Brain | `Brain`, `ExecutiveBrain` | — |

### 7.3 Functions and Methods

- `snake_case`
- Verbs for actions: `load_memory`, `create_mission`, `retrieve`, `orchestrate`
- Boolean predicates: `is_*`, `should_*`, `has_*`
  - `should_remember`, `is_step_completed`

### 7.4 Variables

- `snake_case`
- Avoid single-letter except loop indices
- Meaningful names: `orchestrator_results` not `res2`

### 7.5 Constants

- `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` in `config/settings.py` and module-level constants
- Example: `TITAN_NAME`, `VERSION`, `DEFAULT_MEMORY_PATH`

### 7.6 Agent Registry Keys

- Lowercase short keys: `"coding"`, `"research"`, `"planning"`, `"reasoning"`, `"base"`
- New agents register with single-word or snake_case keys consistently

### 7.7 JSON Schema Keys

- English keys in JSON persistence (`active`, `current_step`, `users`) even when values are French
- Do not rename JSON keys without migration

### 7.8 Prohibited Names

- `temp`, `test123`, `new_module`, `final_final`
- Generic `utils.py` without domain prefix — use `memory_utils.py`, `prompt_utils.py`, etc.

