## 11. Testing Requirements

### 11.1 Policy

**All new modules require tests.** All bug fixes require regression tests when `tests/` exists.

Until `tests/` is created, first engineering task for any new subsystem is scaffold `tests/` with pytest.

### 11.2 Framework

Use **pytest**.

```
tests/test_memory_retriever.py
tests/test_mission_manager.py
tests/test_task_manager.py
```

### 11.3 What Must Be Tested

| Area | Minimum Tests |
|------|---------------|
| Memory retrieval | Keyword relevance, empty memory, user isolation |
| Memory decider/classifier | Trigger keywords, category assignment |
| Mission manager | Step creation, completion, mission completion state |
| State manager | Load/save, update_after_response |
| Task manager | Routing rules produce expected agent lists |
| Agent selector | Keyword routing |
| Task evaluator | Completion keyword detection (careful with false positives) |
| Prompt assembly | Required sections present given inputs |

### 11.4 What Not to Test (Initially)

- Live OpenAI API calls in CI — mock `LLM.ask`
- Actual clock time — mock `TimeTool`

### 11.5 Test Data

Use temporary directories for JSON persistence tests:

```python
tmp_path = Path(tmp_path)
manager = StateManager(file_path=tmp_path / "titan_state.json")
```

Never write tests that modify real `data/` in repo during CI.

### 11.6 Coverage Goal

Target 70%+ on managers and pure logic modules. Brain integration tests may be smoke-level initially.

### 11.7 Running Tests

When introduced:

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
```

All tests must pass before merge.

