## 19. Configuration Management

### 19.1 Layers

| Layer | Location | Content |
|-------|----------|---------|
| Static app config | `config/settings.py` | Name, version, default paths |
| Secrets | `.env` | API keys |
| Runtime state | `data/*.json` | Missions, memory, state |
| Feature flags | `config/settings.py` (future) | Debug mode, logging level |

### 19.2 Adding Configuration

1. Non-secret → `settings.py` with UPPER_SNAKE_CASE name
2. Secret → environment variable documented in `.env.example`
3. Never hardcode paths absolute to one machine — use relative paths from project root

### 19.3 Default Paths

Memory and state managers use relative paths:

```python
file_path="data/long_term_memory.json"
```

Override via constructor parameter for tests.

### 19.4 Feature Flags (Future)

```python
DEBUG_BRAIN = os.getenv("TITAN_DEBUG_BRAIN", "false").lower() == "true"
```

Use flags instead of commenting code paths.

