## 26. Additional Engineering Policies

### 26.1 REPL Session Loop

`Titan.start()` owns the session loop. Exit commands: `exit`, `quit`, `stop`, `bye` (case insensitive).

Do not remove exit handling.

Conversation history is in-memory only unless explicitly persisted in future.

### 26.2 Internationalization

Product targets French-first users. Code may use English identifiers. Error messages to Nolan/Ibrahim in French.

Keyword routing must support French and common English tech terms (`python`, `code`, `remember`).

### 26.3 Git and Commits

- Commit only when user requests
- Never commit `.env` or `data/` personal notes if policy added to gitignore
- Clear commit messages describing why

### 26.4 Cursor-Specific Behavior

When working in this repo:

- Apply this rulebook on every task (`alwaysApply: true`)
- Prefer implementing over describing
- Run commands to verify when possible
- Do not summarize architectural docs when user asks for full detail

